.about-section#about
  .about-text
    I am an Associate Professor (without indefinite tenure) at
    =link_to "Carnegie Mellon University's", "https://www.cmu.edu"
    =link_to "Human-Computer Interaction Institute.", "https://www.hcii.cmu.edu"
    I am also co-founder and Chief Technology Officer of
    =link_to "FuguUX,", "https://www.fuguux.com"
    an early-stage start-up dedicated to improving web usability.
  .about-text
    At CMU, I direct the
    =link_to "SPUD (Security, Privacy, Usability and Design) Lab.", "https://cs.cmu.edu/~spudlab"
    Our work, at the intersection of HCI, AI and cybersecurity, is oriented around answering:
    %strong How can we design systems that empower people with improved agency over their personal data and experiences online?
  .research-directions
    %p Some key research directions include:
    .research-dir
      %b AI Privacy for Practitioners:
      =link_to "Privy (CHI HM)", "https://www.sauvik.me/papers/69/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "AI Privacy Taxonomy (CHI BP)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/51/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "Barriers to AI Privacy Work (USENIX SEC DP)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/47/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "Designing for AI Privacy (CSCW HM)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/31/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
    .research-dir
      %b Human-AI Teaming for Usable S&P:
      =link_to "AI Privacy Risk Estimates (CHI)", "https://www.sauvik.me/papers/70/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "Imago Obscura (UIST)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/66/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "Informed Disclosure Decisions (CSCW)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/58/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
    .research-dir
      %b Evaluating Language Model Privacy:
      =link_to "Agent Decisions Reveal Bias (FAccT)", "https://www.sauvik.me/papers/64/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "VLM Geolocation Privacy (EMNLP)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/57/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "VLM Contextual Integrity (ICLR)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/71/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
    .research-dir
      %b Human-centered Adversarial ML:
      =link_to "Subversive AI (NeurIPS workshop)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/27/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "Human-acceptability of Anti-Facial Recognition (CSCW)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/49/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "Data Defenses against LLMs (pre-print)", "https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.13138", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
    .research-dir
      %b Privacy Collective Action & Governance:
      =link_to "Orchestrating Distributed Collectives (CHI)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/39/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "Taxonomy of Lived Privacy Harms (FAccT)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/42/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "Privacy for the People (IEEE S&P Mag)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/32/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
    .research-dir
      %b Physically-intuitive Privacy and Security:
      =link_to "Smart Webcam Cover (IMWUT)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/35/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "Powering for Privacy (USENIX SEC)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/46/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "On-demand RFID (USEC)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/62/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
    .research-dir
      %b Social Cybersecurity:
      =link_to "Social Proof & Security (CCS)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/9/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "SoK: Social Cybersecurity (Oakland)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/36/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
      =link_to "Group Security Decisions (CHI HM)", "https://sauvikdas.com/papers/23/serve", class: "project-highlight", target: "_blank"
  .about-text
    %p
      %a.awards-filter-link#awardsFilterLink{href: "#publications"}
        A few of my papers have been recognized with awards
      \: a best paper at UbiComp (2013) and CHI (2024), a distinguished paper at SOUPS (2020) and USENIX Security (2024), five best paper honorable mentions at CHI (2016, 2017, 2020, 2024, 2026), a best paper honorable mention at CSCW (2021), and an honorable mention for the NSA's Best Scientific Cybersecurity Paper (2014). My lab's work has been generously supported by the NSF, Facebook, Georgia Tech, and CMU. My work has also been covered by the popular press, including features on The Atlantic, The Financial Times and Dark Reading.

.recruiting-box#recruiting
  .recruiting-status Recruiting Status: Not Recruiting
  %p.recruiting-title Prospective Ph.D. Students
  .recruiting-body
    While I am not currently looking for new Ph.D. students, I encourage you to apply to the
    =link_to "HCII Ph.D. program", "https://www.hcii.cmu.edu/academics/phd-hci"
    at Carnegie Mellon and mention my name in your application. I'm afraid that I am unlikely to respond
    to cold e-mails due to time constraints.
  .recruiting-ctas
    = link_to "Watch PhD Application Advice Video", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JqD2arlzXVE", class: "btn-sd btn-sd-secondary", target: "_blank"
    = link_to "Read Academic Blog", "https://sauvik-das.medium.com/", class: "btn-sd btn-sd-ghost", target: "_blank"
    = link_to "Browse Publications", "#publications", class: "btn-sd btn-sd-ghost"


%div#students
  = react_component('StudentsContainer', currentStudents: @currentStudents, alums: @alums)

%div#publications
= react_component('TabContainer',
    papersUrl: papers_url(format: :json),
    paperAssets: @paperAssetMap,
    paperPollInterval: 10000,
    awardsUrl: awards_url(format: :json),
    courses: @courses,
    currentStudents: @currentStudents,
    alums: @alums)
%noscript
  .about-text
    JavaScript is disabled. You can still access papers directly via the
    = link_to "publications index", papers_path(format: :json)
    and each PDF link from that list.

:javascript
  (function() {
    var link = document.getElementById('awardsFilterLink');
    if (!link) return;
    link.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      document.getElementById('publications').scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
      setTimeout(function() {
        window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('setActiveFilter', { detail: { filter: 'Award-winning' } }));
      }, 300);
    });
  })();

- if @structured_papers.present?
  %script{type: "application/ld+json"}
    = raw(@structured_papers_json_ld)
